ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would definitely recommend this course--it was one of the most helpful courses I've taken at Yale, in terms of courses that changed how I listen to music.
It's a Schenker course that relies on Cadwallader/Gagne

MUSI 549 is an introduction to Schenkerian Analysis. It is a chance to become familiar with the viewpoints of a multi-level structural analysis of tonal music, and understand the principles behind the reading and creation of Schenker graphs. I would recommend this class - though check class size before enrolling - especially if the concepts are unfamiliar to you. However, Dr. Poudrier is great about giving individual attention to students that need it.
